definition.value: A vegetable product such as leaves, flowers, seeds and roots that is rich in essential oils and aromatic principles. Used mainly a a condiment.
A brewed drink prepared from roasted seeds, commonly called coffee beans, of the coffee plant.
A beverage prepared from the cured leaves of Camellia sinensis by combination with hot or boiling water.
A fish food product includes products made from any fish species (aquatic vertebrate with gills and fins).
A dairy food product has mammilian milk or a milk component as an ingredient.

label.value: milk or milk based food product

definition.value: Beer is a fermented cereal beverage resulting from the fermentation most commonly of malted barley (though wheat, corn, or rice may included), by a yeast, most commonly Saccharomyces cerevisiae, and flavored by dried flowers of hops, Humulus lupulus.

Any plant food product which, typically, is constituted by intact parts from one or more annual plants cultivated as field and garden crops in the open and under glass, and used almost exclusively for food.
A one-celled fruit (pod) usually dehiscing down both sutures, and having the seed attached along a ventral suture. (Roubik 1995)

Regarding American regulatory aspects of egg products, see this summary:
https://www.politico.com/agenda/story/2016/03/crazy-us-chicken-egg-regulation-graphic-000077
A hen egg food product is any food product consisting mainly of hen eggs or derivatives.
Cider, hard apple cider, or hard cider in the US, is an alcoholic beverage made from the fermented juice of apples.
A food involving whipped and cooked milk, sugar and egg yolk mixtures.

A ground beef product is made of beef that has been finely chopped with a knife or a meat grinder (American English) or mincing machine (British English). Ground beef is used in many recipes including hamburgers and spaghetti Bolognese.

A food product from a category of domestic birds kept for meat, eggs, and feathers including fowl such as chickens, turkeys, and waterfowls such as domestic ducks and geese and other meat birds such as pigeons and doves and games birds including pheasants.
A turkey meat food product is any food product made predominantly of turkey parts.

Cantaloupe (also known as muskmelon (India and the United States), mushmelon, rockmelon (in Australian states and in New Zealand), sweet melon, spanspek (South Africa), or capuchin (Scotland) refers to a variety of the Cucumis melo species in the Cucurbitaceae family.
A family of hard Italian cheeses made from sheep milk.
